	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 23.30.15. Games were given in his honor by his sons." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1271> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1271" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 23.30.15." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1270> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1270" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "According to Liv. 23.30.15 Aemilius was twice Consul (quib' PCRMA; qui bis C\n   \n    4\n   \n   M\n   \n    1\n   \n   vel M\n   \n    2\n   \n   DAvValla), but no occasion is listed in Fast. Cap. before 222, and it is unlikely that he was elected a Consul Suffectus between 221 and 219, since all the regular incumbents survived, unless, as Degrassi (117) suggests, one of them was vitio creatus. As a patrician he could not have been elected in place of C.Atilius Regulus who died in office in 225. Weissenborn omits bis from his text of Livy, but it is retained by Conway and Walters." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1227> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1227" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap., with Eepidus for Lepidus; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod. (M. Oblicius); Zon. 8.18; and on Lepidus, Polyb. 2.21.7; Liv. 23.30.15; cf. CIL 1\n     .2.617-620; see Degrassi 44f., 117, 440f. Both Consuls were sent to Sardinia, where they captured spoils which they later lost to the Corsicans (Zon. 8.18). On Publicius, see Lübker no. 4." .
